# Local CodeQL

When fixing GitHub Code Scanning / CodeQL alerts on server or mail UI code, validate with the repo Makefile (same config as CI — see `.github/codeql/README.md`).

**Prerequisites:** CodeQL CLI on `PATH` (`brew install codeql`).

**Commands (repo root):**

| Command | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `make codeql-go` | Go server scan + `elvish/go-models` MaD pack (default) |
| `make codeql-summary-go` | Text summary after `codeql-go` |
| `make codeql-js` | JavaScript (`static/mail/`, etc.) |
| `make codeql-all` | Go + JS |
| `make codeql-clean` | Delete `.codeql/` |

**Cursor:** **Terminal → Run Task…** (or `Cmd+Shift+P` → “Tasks: Run Task”) → pick **CodeQL: Go** or **CodeQL: Go + summary**.

**Outputs:** `.codeql/results/go.sarif` (gitignored). Optional: install the recommended **CodeQL** extension to browse SARIF.

Do not add `packs: - local:` to `codeql-config.yml` — CodeQL 2.25 rejects it at init.
